    "recap_headline": "Akron Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AKRON, Ohio --\nFloyd McKenna\ndominated on Saturday, striking out eight UMass hitters over 3.2 innings of work, but it was not enough as the Akron Zips lost to the Minutemen 5-4.\nBrody Chrisman\ncompiled three hits, driving in a run and walking once to leads the Zips offense.\nBlake Bowen\ndrew three walks against the Minutemen.\nIn addition to his eight strikeouts, McKenna went 3.2 shutout innings without giving up a hit and walking one for Akron (8-9, 2-2).\nElijah Griffith\n(2-1) took the loss for Akron.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nTrailing 4-0, the Zips first put runs on the board in the first inning. Akron managed to push across two runs in the inning.\nThe Zips kept the deficit at 4-2 before closing the gap further in the third. Akron scored once on an RBI single off the bat of\nBrody Chrisman\n, which brought the score to 4-3 in favor of the Minutemen.\nUMass built their lead to 5-3 before the Akron offense got going, reducing that lead to 5-4 in the fifth. The Zips were unable to get any closer, as neither team scored again in the ballgame.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Chrisman led the Zips, compiling three hits in the ballgame.\n\u00bb McKenna fanned eight Minutemen hitters.\n\u00bb Zips pitchers combined to strike out 12 UMass hitters.\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the first, when it pushed two runs across.\n\u00bb Akron left 12 runners stranded on base in the loss.\n\u00bb The Zips out-hit the Minutemen at a 6-4 clip.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 37 UMass hitters in the game, allowing eight ground balls and seven fly balls while striking out 12.\n\u00bb The Zips drew 10 walks from UMass pitching.\n\u00bb Chrisman led the Zips at the plate, going 3 for 4 with a double and an RBI.\nWHAT'S NEXT?\nAkron and UMass conclude the series on Sunday, March 15, at 12 p.m."
